Installation of AMI systems in each DisCo

actual.value: 7,060 AMI meters were installed, plus an additional 879 legacy meters, totaling 7,939 MT clients (100%)and 2,326 BT clientsintegrated into the AMI

title.narrative: Introduction of best practices for environmental and social management

target.value: Manuals adopted in the six Distribution Companies

actual.value: Five of the ten expected products have been delivered. These are: (1) Report on Social & Environmental activites developed by theEDEs; (2) report on the norms & procedures of the energy firms in Brazil; (3) Report identifying and consolidating strengths andbestpractices observed in the firms, seeing what can be replicated among the EDEs; (4) Report compiling an analysis of the federal,state and municipal laws in the areas where Eletrobras engages, that shall be part of the adopted guidelines; and (5) Environmentalmanual for works, with the uniqueness of each EDE.

title.narrative: Full implementation of the CMS in the six DisCos

target.value: CMS implemented in the six DisCos

actual.value: During the project implementation, an independent evaluation of Eletrobras' existing AJURI CMS system took place in late 2013. Theoutcome of the evaluation was that the system was deemed adequate, with only some strengthening needed to the customer base system.As such, this indicator is is considered achieved.

title.narrative: Full implementation of ERPs in the six DisCos

target.value: ERP implemented in the six DisCos

actual.value: For the ERP, in order to maintain consistency with other Eletrobras companies, the SAP system had been chosen. However, the licensecost, which was high, could not be covered by the Bank's loan. At the same time this discussion was ongoing, the Board ofEletrobras started exploring the possibility of privatizing the six DISCOs, and the expectation is that the company that acquiredeach DISCO would have their own system to put in place. As such, this indicator is considered not achieved.

title.narrative: Adoption and implementation of environmental and social guidelines across six DisCos

baseline.value: Environmental and social guidelines not adopted

target.value: Guidelines adopted in the six DisCos

actual.value: Five of the ten expected products have been delivered. These are: (1) Report on Social & Environmental activites developed by theEDEs; (2) report on the norms & procedures of the energy firms in Brazil; (3) Report identifying and consolidating strengths andbestpractices observed in the firms, seeing what can be replicated among the EDEs; (4) Report compiling an analysis of the federal,state and municipal laws in the areas where Eletrobras engages, that shall be part of the adopted guidelines; and (5) Environmentalmanual for works, with the uniqueness of each EDE.

title.narrative: UGP functioning and progress reports provided for project

actual.value: While there has been some turnover in the UGP staffing, appropriate measures have been put into place to ensure it keepsfunctioning satisfactorily, following Project Management Institute (PMI) norms.

title.narrative: Effectiveness of social action and communication programs

baseline.value: No social action and communication programs

target.value: 70% of total consumers in survey areas are aware of messages95% of total DisCos staff understand messages

actual.value: The first two programs were evaluated in April 2014 with varying results. In terms of population aware of campaigns, thepercentages were: Acre 41.8%, Alagoas 29.6%, Amazonas 21%, Piaui 32.3%, Rondonia 51.6% and Roraima 15%. Of these, the percentagesthat thoughtthe messages were clear are: Acre 94.1%, Alagoas 57.6%, Amazonas 76.1%, Piaui 74.4%, Rondonia 68.4% and Roraima56.4%.The Campaigns were using all types of media (TV, radio, newspapers and outdoors), and the findings from the initialevaluation are being used to further customize the next campaigns to ensure the best medium is being used.
